<br>
So here goes:<br>
<br>
Solo not Dire Charm: Do no damage, pet takes 75%, you get 25%. Do 1 point of damage, pet takes 33%, you get 66%.  Do 50% or more damage you get full exp.<br>
<br>
A good trick I have employed to get full exp some of the time is as your charm gets lower and lower on life, keep your pet equal to the mobs life.  Once the mob starts running, back off your pet, root the mob, break charm, root your former pet, then nuke them both dead.<br>
<br>
This will net you 100% exp on both those mobs.<br>
<br>
Also as a bonus, lets say your pet is whacking away on a mob and the mob starts running at low life then your charm breaks.  Root your former pet, then root the mob and blast it dead, then recharm your former pet and continue on pulling.<br>
<br>
When charm breaks it resets the damage calculator to zero.  Since you do not have a pet to soak exp, it all goes to you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyways that is just a little snippet on soloing and charm exp.  If you have any questions, feel free to shoot me a tell in game.<br>
<br>
<br>
