<br>
That would be more mana costly then simply rooting and recharming your first pet that is buffed already, fight another mob and get both down to low life.  Then break charm, root both and nuke them for full exp.<br>
<br>
That's how I do it anyways and I made 61 in 14 days /played time so I must be doing something right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A good rule of thumb is recharm your pet if charm breaks if it has enough life left to go through another mob to bring it to near death.  Just keep it balanced so both the pet and mob are down to 5% +/- life, nuke both for 100% exp and grab yourself another pet.  gtg<br>
<br>
Is my way the best?...No everyone has their own methods.  This is how I do it and I have spent many many hours in PoD and still am.  This is what I have found to get the most out of my time and mana <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trump13>Trump13</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/03 12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=220.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charming exp when soloing</span><hr size=1> Shrug, I have my epic so haste isn't an issue.<br>
<br>
Also, slow will nullify the effects of haste until it wears off, so you can use that instead of haste to save mana (use a lower level slow).<br>
<br>
Also, a rooted pet is as useless to me as mana is to a rogue.  Have you tried using your 20-second level-4 mez?  Works 3000x better.<br>
<br>
Yes, if your pet is still at like 80%, recharm it by all means.  But 30-40%? screw it, new pet.  And honestly, at 60 in the tier one planes, you can still nuke for decent damage.<br>
<br>
Be ready for the rules to change when you get to charming tier 2/3 creatures.<br>
